Implementation of Dig Dug Phases 1-4:

Backend: GameSave model, Pydantic schemas (slot_number 1-3 validation), controller with upsert pattern, blueprint with /game page and /api/game/saves REST endpoints, Alembic migration.

Frontend: Complete game engine in TypeScript - constants, types, deterministic level generator, Player/Enemy/Pooka/Fygar/Rock entities, GameEngine with 60fps loop + 5-layer collision detection + state transitions + scoring, Canvas renderer with geometric primitives.

React: DigDugGame component, GameHUD, PauseOverlay, SaveLoadModal, useKeyboard (ref-based for zero re-renders), useGameSaves hook.

Key decisions:
- Pydantic e.errors() needs include_url=False, include_context=False for JSON serialization
- Canvas mocked in vitest with all 2D context methods
- requestAnimationFrame mocked with vi.spyOn to prevent infinite loops
- Tests use SQLite in-memory via db.create_all() - no migration needed
- Pre-commit mypy requires type annotations (used Any for test client param)

Tests: 23 pytest (11 game + 12 hello) + 15 vitest (11 game + 4 hello) all passing
Lint (flake8+eslint) and typecheck (mypy+tsc) clean
